//version568//This version of the guide was updated for version 5.6.8 of the online packages.

You may adjust some of the Sumac online settings by altering the values described here.

************************************************************************************
* THIS IS NOT THE FILE CONTAINING THE SETTINGS. IT ONLY DESCRIBES THEM.
* 
* THE FILE THAT CONTAINS THE SETTINGS MUST BE CALLED 'sumac_parameter.settings'
* AND IT MUST RESIDE IN THE 'user' FOLDER WITHIN THE ONLINE FOLDER ON THE WEBSITE.
*
* A SAMPLE VERSION OF THAT FILE IS PROVIDED WITH ALL SETTINGS INACTIVE.
************************************************************************************

These are the settings you may adjust: (examples and normal settings are in a later list)

	source		the address of the system running the Sumac server
				an IP address (e.g. '206.248.154.122') or known host name (e.g. 'localhost' or 'www.google.com')

	port		the port that the Sumac server is listening on on that system
				a number (e.g. '80')

	userdata	values to be passed through to Sumac with every HTTP request
				a user-defined string

	[nouserpw	parameter no longer used as of version 5.6.5; see new parameters '*2nouserpw' below.]

	frequency	the option to solicit monthly donations rather than a single donation, or both
				the word 'combined' to solicit both together - the default for an organisation with Pledge Days configured in Sumac
				the word 'once' to solict a single donation - the default for an organisation with no Pledge Days configured in Sumac
				the word 'monthly' to solicit monthly donations
				(only the first letter being 'c' or 'o' or 'm' is really checked)
				only the Donations package uses this

	amounttopay	the fixed amount of a single or monthly donation
				a decimal currency amount with no currency symbol (e.g. '20' or '20.00' for twenty dollars)
				when you use this parameter, you will probably want to name the amount in the 'title' or 'titlem' as well
				only the Donations package uses this

	paybutton	the label for the button that submits the donation request
				any text, preferably a single word in upper case
				only the Donations package uses this

	dptitle		text to provide the major title for all the Donation/Payment pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Donations package uses this (see 'title' below for use when started as single package)

	cutitle		text to provide the major title for all the Contact-management pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Contact-management package uses this (see 'title' below for use when started as single package)

	mrtitle		text to provide the major title for all the Membership pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Membership package uses this (see 'title' below for use when started as single package)

	totitle		text to provide the major title for all the Ticket Ordering pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Ticketing package uses this (see 'title' below for use when started as single package)

	crtitle		text to provide the major title for all the Course Registration pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Courses package uses this (see 'title' below for use when started as single package)

	title		text to provide the major title for all the pages (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				ONLY USED WITH SINGLE-PACKAGE START - otherwise use dptitle,cutitle,mrtitle,totitle,crtitle

	titlem		text to provide the major title for all the pages for Monthly Donations (extended by ' unavailable' on the failure page)
				any text
				only the Donations package uses this, and only with frequency set to monthly

	titlecolour	the colour of the major title on all the pages
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'Pink') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#666666')

	dppayment	text to act as instructions above the payment panel on the final Donation/Payment page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Donations  package use this (see 'payment' below for use when started as single package)

	mrpayment	text to act as instructions above the payment panel on the final Membership page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Membership package use this (see 'payment' below for use when started as single package)

	topayment	text to act as instructions above the payment panel on the final Ticket Ordering page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package use this (see 'payment' below for use when started as single package)

	payment		text to act as instructions above the payment panel on the final page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				the Donations, Ticketing, and Membership packages use this
				ONLY USED WITH SINGLE-PACKAGE START - otherwise use dppayment,mrpayment,topayment

	order		text to act as instructions above the ticket ordering panel when there is nothing to pay
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	ordernd		text to act as instructions above the ticket ordering panel when there is nothing to pay and no further details to supply
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	update		text to act as instructions above the contact detail update panel on the final page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Contact-management package uses this

	renew		text to act as instructions above the membership renewal panel on the final page when there is a choice of plans
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Membership package uses this

	norenew		text to act as instructions above the membership renewal panel on the final page when no plans are available
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Membership package uses this

	dpaddcontact text to act as instructions above the contact-details panel on the Donation/Payment login page when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Donations package use this (see 'addcontact' below for use when started as single package)

	toaddcontact text to act as instructions above the contact-details panel on the Ticket Ordering login page when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package use this (see 'addcontact' below for use when started as single package)

	craddcontact text to act as instructions above the contact-details panel on the Course Registration login page when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Courses package use this (see 'addcontact' below for use when started as single package)

	addcontact	text to act as instructions above the contact-details panel when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				the Donations and Ticketing and Courses packages use this
				ONLY USED WITH SINGLE-PACKAGE START - otherwise use dpaddcontact,toaddcontact,craddcontact

	dpaddorlogin text to act as instructions above the combined login and contact-details panel on the Donation/Payment login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Donations package use this (see 'addorlogin' below for use when started as single package)

	toaddorlogin text to act as instructions above the combined login and contact-details panel on the Ticket Ordering login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package use this (see 'addorlogin' below for use when started as single package)

	craddorlogin text to act as instructions above the combined login and contact-details panel on the Course Registration login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Courses package use this (see 'addorlogin' below for use when started as single package)

	addorlogin	text to act as instructions above the combined login and contact-details panel when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				the Donations and Ticketing packages use this
				ONLY USED WITH SINGLE-PACKAGE START - otherwise use dpaddorlogin,toaddorlogin,craddorlogin

	mrloginwopw	text to act as instructions above the combined login and contact-details panel on the Membership login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Membership package uses this (see 'loginwopw' below for use when started as single package)

	culoginwopw	text to act as instructions above the login panel on the Contact-management login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Contact-management package uses this (see 'loginwopw' below for use when started as single package)

	loginwopw	text to act as instructions above the  Contact-management login panel or above the combined login and contact-details panel on the Membership login page when no password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				the Membership and Contact-management packages use this
				ONLY USED WITH SINGLE-PACKAGE START - otherwise use mrloginwopw,culoginwopw

	login		text to act as instructions above the login panel when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				all packages but the Contact-management package uses this

	culogin		text to act as instructions above the login panel when a password is required
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Contact-management package uses this

	password	text to act as instructions above the forgotten-password panel on the login page
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)

	omitfields	a list of contact-detail fields that are NOT to be requested from the donor
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpm' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				the Donations and Ticketing packages use this
				(March 2014: parameter not used by New Generation packages; see 'global' parameters)

	mustfields	a list of contact-detail fields that MUST to be supplied by the donor as well as Email and Last Name
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpm' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				the Donations, Ticketing, and Contact-management packages use this
				(March 2014: parameter not used by New Generation packages; see 'global' parameters)

	fontsize	the fontsize for the text on all the pages
				one of the values 'small', 'normal' or 'big'

	fonttype	the font family for the text on all the pages
				any valid font style (e.g. 'serif') or fontname (e.g. 'Garamond')

	textcolour	the colour of the text on all the pages
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'blue' or 'DarkSlateGray') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#666666')

	bodycolour	the colour of the background to all the pages
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'Cornsilk' or 'Burlywood') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#DDD')

	sbbgcolour	the colour of the background to the shopping basket ('What you are buying') panel on all pages
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'wheat' or 'Lavender') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#FFFF00')
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	etbgcolour	the colour of the background to the event theatre layout or the event title for general admission
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'Khaki') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#FFFF00')
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	ppbgcolour	the colour of the background to the payment panel on the final page
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'crimson' or 'Chartreuse') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#7FFFD4')
				the Donations, Ticketing, and Membership packages use this

	sbavcolour	the colour of the background to the seat block availability title and pseudo-tickets
				any valid HTML colour
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	detailwide	the width in pixels of the frame in which theatre event details are displayed
				a number
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	detailtall	the height in pixels of the frame in which theatre event details are displayed
				a number
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	navbgfolder	the subfolder of the PHP folder in which the background images for the navbars are stored
				any existing subfolder, such as 'user' or 'user/images/' (note: forward slashes and final slash)
				only the Ticketing package uses this at present

	navbgfilext	the file extension/type of the background images for the navbars
				'jpg' or 'gif' are will work; others may not
				only the Ticketing package uses this at present

	connection	text informing the user that the attempted connection to the Sumac server has failed
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)

	badresponse	text informing the user that the Sumac server has given an invalid response
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)

	othererror	text informing the user of any other fatal system error|
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)

	dateformat	format for displaying dates
				a pattern containing combinations of "yyyy', "yyy", "yy", "mmmm", "mmm", "mm", "m",
				"dd", "d", "ww", "w" and separating characters

	dateformat1	format for displaying dates in the course catalog (defaults to dateformat)
				only the Courses package uses this

	dateformat2	format for displaying dates in the personal history lists (defaults to dateformat)
				only the Courses package uses this

	sortcolumn	the number of the course catalog column to sort the catalog list on
				1(course names),2(dates),3(durations),4(instructors), or 0 for the order in which Sumac sent the list
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	sortdir		the direction - ascending or descending - which the list should be sorted in
				'a' or 'd'
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	deffeename	name for the "session fee" cost element in course registration
				any text
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	paycourse	text to act as instructions above the payment panel for course registration
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Courses package uses this at present (see 'payment' above for other packages)

	payaccount	text to act as instructions above the payment panel for course payments other than registration
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Courses package uses this at present (see 'payment' above for other packages)

	donationlnk	whether or not a link to the Donation package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	ticketlnk	whether or not a link to the Ticketing package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	renewallnk	whether or not a link to the Membership package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	contactlnk	whether or not a link to the Contact-management package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	courseslnk	whether or not a link to the Courses package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	directlnk	whether or not a link to the Directories package should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	leavelnk	whether or not the 'Leave' exit-link should be included in the Sumac navigation bar
				the word 'true' to include the link (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				(March 2014: the New Donation package has no Sumac navigation bar)

	notheatre	for efficiency, to exclude the loading of theatre data when the Ticketing package will not be used
				the word 'true' to exclude the theatre data (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	nocatalog	for efficiency, to exclude the loading of course catalog data when the Courses package will not be used
				the word 'true' to exclude the catalog data (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	nodirectory	for efficiency, to exclude the loading of directory data when the Directories package will not be used
				the word 'true' to exclude the directory data (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	nograntform	for efficiency, to exclude the loading of grantform data when the Review Grant package will not be used
				the word 'true' to exclude the directory data (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	nooversumac	suppress user's 'over_sumac.css' file so as to confirm that it is not responsible for problems
				the word 'true' to suppress the CSS (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	precursym	the symbol to be prefixed to numbers that represent currency amounts
				any string of one or more characters such as '$' or '£' or 'USD '

	omitfinhist	omit the financial section of the Personal History page of the Courses package
				the word 'true' to omit the section (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	omiteduhist	omit the education section of the Personal History page of the Courses package
				the word 'true' to omit the section (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	omitformsum	omit the forms summary section of the Personal History page of the Courses package
				the word 'true' to omit the section (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	omitcnavbar	omit the navigation bar of the the Courses package
				the word 'true' to omit the navigation bar (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	formflag1	the value to be shown in a completed form when a flag field has the value '1'
				any string, e.g. 'yes', 'true', 'on'
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	formflag0	the value to be shown in a completed form when a flag field has the value '0'
				any string, e.g. 'no', 'false', 'off'
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	noeventsnow	text to display when there are no ticketable events
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package uses this at present

	nocoursenow	text to display when there are no courses to register for
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	formsopen	flag to indicate default behaviour in opening forms for update or review
				the value '1' to open forms in a new tab or window, or '2' to open them in the current one
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	mandfldcol	the colour of the text of the labels of a form's mandatory fields - fields that MUST be filled in
				any valid HTML colour (e.g. 'Pink') or a hex-coded RGB value (e.g. '#666666')
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	selectevent	text to display in the dropdown for a production's event/performance list
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	commemform	the number of lines the commemoration/dedication question occupies in the donation form
				one of the values '0' (meaning the question is omitted), '1', or '2'
				only the Donations package uses this

	commemtext1	text to be used for the first or only line of the commemoration/dedication question
				any text, but if commemform is '1' it should be short
				only the Donations package uses this
	
	commemtext2	text to be used for the second line of the commemoration/dedication question
				any text, but it should be short
				only the Donations package uses this

	chosentext1	text to act as instructions for what a user should do after choosing tickets for an event when there is only one event available
				any text; the string '%0' will be replaced by the label of the 'Check out' link
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	chosentext2	text to act as instructions for what a user should do after choosing tickets for an event when there other events available
				any text; the string '%0' will be replaced by the label of the 'Check out' link, and '%1'  will be replaced by the label of the 'Event' link
				only the Ticketing package uses this

	incpaynote	include a note from the payee in the ticket payment screen
				the word 'true' to include the note (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Ticketing package uses this at present

	paynotetext	the label for the text box that is to contain the note from the payee
				any text (you can use '<br />' in the text to force the start of a new line)
				only the Ticketing package uses this at present

	optnatext	the text for a membership optional extra that is not applicable to a particular plan
				any text, but it should be short
				only the Membership package uses this

	catalogurl	the URL of the page for the catalog (or course list) when using the No Catalog version of Sumac's Courses package
				a valid URL
				only the Courses package uses this

	selectorht	the height of a multiple-selection 'dropdown' list in a directory selector
				any valid HTML measurement (e.g. '100px', '3cm', '25%')
				only the Directories package uses this

	selectorbg	the background colour for the directory selector panels
				any valid HTML colour (see examples in other parameters)
				only the Directories package uses this

	selectedbg	the background colour for a selected choice in a multiple-selection 'dropdown' list in a directory selector
				any valid HTML colour (see examples in other parameters)
				only the Directories package uses this

	resultsshow	flag to indicate default behaviour in showing the results of a directory search
				the value '1' to show results in a new tab or window, or '2' to show them in the current one
				only the Directories package uses this

	resultsformat	flag to indicate default behaviour in formatting the results of a directory search
				the value '1' to format entries as a list, or '2' to format entries as a table
				only the Directories package uses this

	eitherformat	to allow the user to choose between the two formats for the results of a directory search
				the word 'true' to allow the choice (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Directories package uses this

	sessexpiry	the maximum number of seconds to allow a user to respond before forcing a session restart
				any number

	combdonpref	when combining monthly and one-time donations, the choice of which to place first in the payment panel
				either 'monthly' or 'once' (all that is really checked is whether the first letter is 'm')
				only the Donations package uses this

	sepmontext	a switch to select separate instructions and button-label for the monthly donation
				before version 5.1.2, the top instructions and the DONATE button were sourced from the same place;
				if this is 'true', monthly donation instructions will be string DI11 and button label will be DL2
				only the Donations package uses this

	attmtblock	the blocksize to use in file-transfer operations for attachments to forms
				a number between 1 and 86016

	singlereg	disallow multiple registrations in a single payment. A second registration will replace the first.
				the word 'true' to allow only one registration per payment (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Courses package uses this at present

	d2asnavlnk	whether or not to connect the Donation link in the navigation bar to the New Donation package
				the word 'true' to connect to the New Donations package (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)

	d2fixedamt	the fixed amount of a single or monthly donation (like 'amounttopay' for old Donations)
				a decimal currency amount with no currency symbol (e.g. '20' or '20.00' for twenty dollars)
				only the New Donations package uses this

	d2amounts	one or more suggested donation amounts for the user to choose between
				a series of one or more decimal currency amounts separated by semi-colons (e.g. '20;50;99.99;1000')
				only the New Donations package uses this

	d2frequency	the option to solicit monthly donations rather than a single donation, or both (like 'frequency' for old Donations)
				the word 'combined' to solicit both together - the default
				the word 'once' to solict a single donation
				the word 'monthly' to specifically solicit monthly donations
				(only the first letter being 'c' or 'o' or 'm' is really checked)
				only the New Donations package uses this

	d2nologin	whether or not to force the user to enter all personal details but without a password
				the word 'true' to force detail entry (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the New Donations package uses this
				
	d2nouserpw	the option to suppress the use of passwords in the New Donations login/identification process
				the word 'true' to leave out passwords (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the New Donations package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the New Donations package uses this in place of 'nouserpw'

	d2omitfields	a list of contact-detail fields that are NOT to be requested from the donor
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpmw' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				only the New Donations package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the New Donations package uses this in place of 'omitfields'

	d2mustfields	a list of contact-detail fields that MUST to be supplied by the donor as well as Email and Last Name
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpm' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				only the New Donations package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the New Donations package uses this in place of 'mustfields'

	d2statesdd	the identifier for a dropdown list of states/provinces that the donor may choose from
				one of 'can', 'us', 'uscan', 'canus', or the filename or URL of a user-supplied list
				if you want to create your own list, you should inspect one or the Sumac dropdown files
				if there is no value for this parameter, the donor must type in their state/province
				only the New Donations package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
	
	d2fundreqd	whether or not the user must select a fund for the donation to apply to
				the word 'true' to force the user to select a fund (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the New Donations package uses this

	d2fundkey	a single search term that replaces the users fund search option and only applies to keywords 
				any string not containing spaces; the user will only be allowed to choose from funds whose keywords
				match this string, partially or completely, disregarding upper and lower case, and searching is disabled
				only the New Donations package uses this

	f2nouserpw	the option to suppress the use of passwords in the Single Form login/identification process
				the word 'true' to leave out passwords (only the first letter  being 't' is really checked)
				only the Single Form package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the Single Form package uses this in place of 'nouserpw'

	f2omitfields	a list of contact-detail fields that are NOT to be requested from the form-requestor
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpmw' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				only the Single Form package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the Single Form package uses this in place of 'omitfields'

	
	f2mustfields	a list of contact-detail fields that MUST to be supplied by the form-requestor as well as Email and Last Name
				any selection of the letters 'fatszcpm' in any order (see list below for meanings)
				only the Single Form package uses this (but see 'global' parameters below)
				the Single Form package uses this in place of 'mustfields'

	f2statesdd	the identifier for a dropdown list of states/provinces that the form-requestor may choose from
