There are also six parameters that CAN ONLY be passed via the href URL
(These are not needed or used by the old start files, 'raods_start.php', 'raots_start.php', etc.)

	resume		can be set to 'false', or just 'f', to ensure that the link starts a new Sumac session
				if omitted (or set to any other value), an existing Sumac session will be continued

	package		the package to be executed
				one of the nine packages 'donation', 'ticketing', 'courses', 'membership', 'contact', 'directories', 'donation2', 'singleform2', 'signup2'
				this parameter may always be omitted when the entry is 'login'
				if it is omitted without entry set to 'login', the link will fail if there is no active Sumac session

	entry		a non-standard starting point for the package; the following values are recognised
				1. 'login'	(available for any package, but only affecting Ticketing and Courses because the other packages all start with login anyway)
				2. 'register'	(only available for Courses; bypasses the catalog presentation)
				3. 'formslist'	(only available for Courses; leads to the Personal History page)
				4. 'finhistory'	(only available for Courses; leads to the Personal History page)
				5. 'eduhistory'	(only available for Courses; leads to the Personal History page)
				6. 'paycourse'	(only available for Courses; leads to the Payment page)

	coursename	the name of the course to be registered for (only meaningful when &entry=register)

	coursedate	the start date of the session of the course to be registered for (only meaningful when &entry=register)

	formname	the name of the form to be submitted for (only meaningful when &package=singleform2)

